COPS in Willowvale have arrested a 17-year-old boy for possession of unlicensed firearm a 7, 65 pistol with two magazines and one round of ammunition. The suspect was arrested on Monday 23 July at about 16:00 at Nquma Locality, Nqadu Village, Willowvale. Colonel Sibongile Soci said the teen is due to appear before the Willowvale Magistrate Court on Tuesday on charges of possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition. The firearm will be sent for ballistic test to establish if it was not used in the commission of crime around Willowvale and the surrounding villages. 